    "comment": "Rationale: Profilin-1 is detected in the the presynapse of rat hippocampus CA1 [Fig3D] and cerebellar cortex [Fig4B & C] as well as the spine in CA1 [Fig3B-D]. The presentence profilin-1 at both the pre- and postsynaptic side was also observed in cultured mouse hippocampal neurons [Fig 5A-C]. The localisation of the immuno-gold label are consistent with the role of profilins as actin regulators.. Experimental description: Figure 3 and 4 is rat tissue \"Adult albino rats (Wistar) were deeply anaesthetized with ketamine (100 mg / kg) and xylazine (5 mg / kg) and perfused through the left ventricle\", Figure 5 is mouse cultured neurons \"Primary cultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared from C57Bl6J mice at postnatal days 0-1 as described previously\" found in the material and methods",
